## `missing-nonbreaking-space`

Flag a plain space where a TeX tie (`~`) belongs, between a word and a cross-reference or citation command (`Figure \ref{x}`, `see \cite{a}`). A tie keeps the word and its number from splitting across a line break. Only the same-line `WORD SPACE \cmd` shape is flagged. The fix is **unsafe** -- inserting a tie changes line breaking -- so `--fix` leaves it alone; `--unsafe-fixes` and the editor code action apply it.

A plain space where a tie belongs before a cross-reference:

```tex
see Figure \ref{fig:plot}
```

```text
warning: missing-nonbreaking-space
 --> example.tex:1:11
  |
1 | see Figure \ref{fig:plot}
  |           ^ missing non-breaking space before `\ref`; use a tie `~` so the reference stays on the same line
```
